Validate a metadata field.
All _process_*() methods correspond to a core metadata field. The method is called with the field's raw value. If the raw value is valid it is returned in its "enriched" form (e.g. ``version.Version`` for the ``Version`` field). If the raw value is invalid, :exc:`InvalidMetadata` is raised (with a cause as appropriate).
